-- S&P cuts UniCredit, Intesa Sanpaolo ratings in Italian banks review
-- 
-- Thu Dec 18, 2014 01:49PM EST
-- None



MILAN, Dec 18 (Reuters) - Ratings agency Standards and Poor's has cut the ratings on Italy's two largest banks UniCredit and Intesa Sanpaolo after a recent downgrade of the country's sovereign rating, the banks said in separate statements.

S&P has reviewed the ratings of other Italian banks. [ID:nWNAB05JGX] UniCredit <CRDI.MI> said its long-term rating was cut by S&P to 'BBB-' while its stand-alone rating was cut to 'BBB-' from 'BBB' with stable outlook. Intesa Sanpaolo <ISP.MI> said S&P cuts its long-term rating to 'BBB-' from 'BBB' with stable outlook.